 >> Is there a secure (encrypting) file system for PCs that uses container
 >> files, like Doublespace does?  Both SFS and Secure Drive encrypt a
 >> partition, so the only access to it is through the driver -- and then
 >> you cannot make non-plaintext backups of an encrypted drive.
 
 >> If they used a container file, the file could be backed up with any
 >> method.  It could even be transported to other systems.

Norton Utilities' "Diskreet" will do that, but I'm told that it uses a weak
implementation of DES.  I'd rather see an encrypting backup program instead.

